Meeting Description:

First Postgraduate Conference ESGHT2010

We invite postgraduate students from the fields of Tourism, Management,=20
Languages and ICT to present papers at the First Postgraduate Conference ES=
GHT
2010 on Friday, 25th June 2010 on topics related to their current research =
area.=20

Call for Papers

Submission guidelines for papers

We are particularly interested in papers in the following areas:

Tourism
- Tourism Marketing=20
- Sociology of Tourism
- Psychology of Tourism
- Cultural Tourism
Management
- Financial Management and Taxation
- Human Resources Management
- Quality Management
Languages
- Applied Linguistics
- Literacy studies

ICT (applied to Tourism, Management or Languages)

Abstracts should be no longer than 300 words and should be submitted via e-
mail attachments (Microsoft Word or Rich Text Format files). Abstracts shou=
ld
not include the author's name or any other identifying information. Abstrac=
ts
will be reviewed anonymously.=20

Abstracts should include:=20
1. The title of the paper=20
2. A list of 3-5 key words describing the area and focus=20
3. The research focus=20
4. The research methodology=20
5. A brief summary of findings (if applicable)=20
6. A short list of key references=20

The e-mail message accompanying the abstract should contain the following=
=20
information:
1. The name(s) of the author(s)
2. Author(s) affiliation(s)=20
3. The title of the paper
4. One (or more) of the above research subareas =20
5. A brief bio-data of the author (up to 40 words)=20
6. Home address
7. The author's e-mail address=20
8. The author's phone number
9. Audiovisual equipment required (besides computer and projector which=20
will be supplied)=20

Submission Deadline=20
Abstracts must be received by 15 February 2010
Authors will be notified of acceptance by 31 March 2010
Please email your abstracts to: seminariopgesght2010@gmail.com
=20
Publication=20
After the conference, participants will be invited to submit their papers i=
n=20
written form (3500 - 4000 words, including references) for publication in o=
ne=20
of the following ESGHT journals: Encontros Cient=EDficos and Dos Algarves.=
=20
Papers will be peer reviewed. =20

For additional information, please consult www.esght.ualg.pt





